The paper presents a novel in-data processing-in-storage architecture based on Resistive Content Addressable Memory (RCAM). This suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of PRINS in various data processing tasks, indicating that it may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The use of RCAM also suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) sub-category. The paper also discusses the parallel processing capabilities of PRINS, which may suggest that it belongs to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of PRINS in various applications, indicating that it may belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
